comments: I had no problem with Prof Eberhardt. She was very responsive,assignments were clear, graded promptly and graded fairly. There were formulas to remember, but that would be the case for any finance class, had nothing to do with this professor.

Worst experience so far with an instructor. Argumentative and unclear about what she requires. She would ask for one thing and then a few assignments later change her mind. She grades promptly and fairly which is nice, but I would avoid taking her courses.
Hands down the worst teacher with whom I have ever interacted. Completely unreasonable and will mark you wrong for arbitrary reasons at a whim. Avoid at all costs.
Provides timely feedback with grades but VERY unreasonable with grading especially considering the difficulty in subject matter.
When she grades your papers is extremely unreasonable. Not helpful at all. Would never take one of her classes ever again>
Not so easy class; great instructor!
